1
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:58,140
ONCE UPON A TIME IN ANATOLIA

2
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:12,711
Izzet, bring him over.

3
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:22,440
Is it here?

4
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,320
Huh?

5
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,358
-No.
-What?

6
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,596
-It's not here.
-You sure?

7
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,916
How do you know it's not here?

8
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:51,470
-The place wasn't like this.
-What?

9
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:53,631
The place wasn't like this.
There was a field.

10
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,439
What sort of field?
On a slope or fiat?

11
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:59,832
Flat. There was like a round tree.

12
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,752
A round tree?

13
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,637
Chief, does he mean
the fountain down beside Kizilkaya?

14
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,472
Oh, the one by whatsitsname..

15
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:11,314
-There's a field there?
-Sure.

16
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:14,479
-So you're saying it's not here.
-No.

17
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:17,109
OK. Take him away, Izzet.

18
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:25,630
Mr Prosecutor, seems there's
another fountain like this down below.

19
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:28,598
He says it's not here,
so I'd guess it's there.

20
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,194
-So it's not here either.
-No. That's what he says.

21
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:36,837
Fine. Let's go then.

22
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:02,552
-We call it 'komus' where I come from.
-Whatever. So one night...

23
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,870
It's late. Everyone's tanked up.

24
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:07,554
-You listening, doctor?
-Of course, chief.

25
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:10,228
So we're all drunk
and the tax officer walks off.

26
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:13,233
I think, he's an ass-licker.
He'll come back with something.

27
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,470
Soon as he sees a big wig,
he gets to work.

28
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:17,358
-That's Nedim.
-Who?

29
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:20,193
-The tax officer at the time.
-No, it was Sinasi.

30
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,713
Nedim came before him.

31
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:26,476
Oh, yes. He'd throw back
his head to talk. Fat and bald.

32
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:30,758
Around two months
after Mr. Galip arrived...

33
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,070
...he got posted somewhere else.

34
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:36,949
Well, he goes off with the waiters.

35
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:40,192
And they come back with three trays.

36
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:43,234
-See a tray and what do you think?
-Kebabs.

37
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:44,913
You'd think kebabs. Meat.

38
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:49,758
But no! It's yoghurt.
What kind of yoghurt?

39
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,668
Not the soupy kind we know.
It's hard as rock.

40
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:57,595
-You need a knife to cut the stuff.
-Sure it wasn't cheese, chief?

41
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:58,960
Cheese?

42
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,270
You think I don't know yoghurt
from cheese, doctor?

43
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,078
What do you take me for?

44
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:05,470
That stuff's delicious, doctor.
Especially in spring.

45
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:10,031
No, it was yoghurt.
But buffalo yoghurt.

46
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,236
Not sheep or whatever,
buffalo yoghurt.

47
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:15,790
They have buffalo stuff at the dairy
down from our quarters.

48
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:19,270
-Where is there a dairy?
-Down from our quarters, sir.

49
00:08:19,440 --> 00:08:22,079
Which quarters are you in?
What dairy?

50
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:24,550
You know that dairy
below our quarters?

51
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,153
-By Kivircik's place?
-Yes, sir.

52
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,072
They sometimes make it there.

53
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:31,312
-That stuff's pasteurized!
-No, it's buffalo. I've tried it.

54
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:33,391
-It kind of smelled.
-It smells if it's good.

55
00:08:33,560 --> 00:08:39,112
Buffalo yoghurt.. Wouldn't I know
if they had it at the corner shop?

56
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:43,799
-I'm crazy about the stuff.
-To be honest, chief, you don't know.

57
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:46,793
I tried it.
But it just seemed to smell a bit.

58
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:51,750
Because it's good. The animals eat
fresh grass in spring, right, doctor?

59
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:55,877
Arab, some people have no taste
for the good things.

60
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:59,157
I mention buffalo yoghurt
and the guy says it smells.

61
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:02,232
He doesn't know the real thing.
What's he used to?

62
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,834
Pasteurized. You can get
pasteurized from any shop.

63
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,434
No, chief. My deceased mother
used to make it.

64
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,033
They can't make it like that now.

65
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:12,636
You know, I see stuff sometimes
that really bugs me.

66
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:15,872
In the supermarket. 'Skimmed' yoghurt.
What the hell is that?

67
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:18,713
'Skimmed' yoghurt.
You'd be ashamed to write the words.

68
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:21,314
There's a good dollop
of cream in buffalo yoghurt.

69
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:24,278
Nedim was in Mr. Galip's time.
That's the guy.

70
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,351
-He was a good man.
-And nice.

71
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:29,990
Nice, meaning harmless.
Harmless passes for nice these days.

72
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:32,799
Useful doesn't come into it, Arab.

73
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:27,758
OK, where is it then?

74
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,160
Well..

75
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,200
Huh?

76
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:34,432
Well, umm...

77
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:38,073
Kenan!

78
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:42,950
-Speak to me! Where is it?
-I don't know.

79
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,118
-I mean, I'd been drinking.
-What?

80
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:47,555
-I'd been drinking.
-Huh?

81
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:50,516
You'd been drinking.

82
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:54,072
-You'd been drinking?
-Yes.

83
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:59,516
-Had your brother been drinking too?
-He doesn't drink.

84
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:05,749
So you don't remember exactly?

85
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:10,351
Say something.
Say there was a tree, anything!

86
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:13,796
Was it up by the fountain
or below the road? Say something!

87
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,040
Ramazan.

88
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,799
Come over here, lad.

89
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:24,675
Can you show me, lad?
Where it was then?

90
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:27,190
Huh? Where was it?

91
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,788
Ramazan, don't be scared now.
Just say where it was.

92
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,079
I don't know.

93
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:33,672
You don't know?

94
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:37,197
You don't know
or you don't remember?

95
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:40,875
-I was asleep.
-What do you mean?

96
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:43,868
Answer me, lad!

97
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,548
-I was asleep.
-Huh?

98
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:47,073
I was asleep.

99
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:49,312
You were asleep.

100
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:56,038
Kenan.

101
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:59,950
Just get your head together
and let's be done with this, huh?

102
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:02,352
Is this the place?

103
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:05,475
-I think so.
-You think so?

104
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:08,149
Over by that fountain, if we...

105
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:10,717
-Over here?
-Yes.

106
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:14,913
Your tree.. The trees are down below.
Or was the tree by the fountain?

107
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,992
It's dark now.
I need to look.

108
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:21,438
Sergeant, point those headlights
this way.

109
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,636
Mehmet, turn the car round
to face the fountain.

110
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,756
Izzet, bring him over.

111
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,318
Is this the place?

112
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,991
Well...

113
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:02,880
Yes?

114
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:10,550
It looks like here, but those trees...

115
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:14,311
-Which trees?
-On a diagonal with those trees...

116
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:17,035
-Yes?
-There was a dug-up field.

117
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:20,870
-You mean ploughed?
-Yes.

118
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:26,633
Come here. Look, this is ploughed.
You mean here?

119
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,759
Huh?

120
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:32,636
Diggers! Over here!

121
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:35,628
Check for any newly dug holes.

122
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:37,399
Quick!

123
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:41,031
Where exactly in the field?

124
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,999
Right by the entrance, or what?

125
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:46,828
-Huh?
-There was a round tree.

126
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,473
What kind of tree?

127
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:51,638
I say that
because it was easy to dig.

128
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:54,713
You say there was a round tree.
What do you mean?

129
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,871
Did you dig under the tree?

130
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:02,633
Kenan, now look here.

131
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:06,160
Are you trying to distract me?

132
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:08,630
It won't get you anywhere.

133
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:12,236
Whatever we talked about
at the police station, that's it.

134
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:15,553
You come out here
and you lose your head.

135
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:20,399
I'm treating you decently.
So be a man and show me the place.

136
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,200
Huh?

137
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,912
Where is it?

138
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:31,674
Is it here?
Hey, is it here?

139
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:51,075
Mr Prosecutor, he says
this isn't the place either.

140
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:54,038
Naci. Didn't you say to me
everything was all set?

141
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:59,309
Yes, Mr Prosecutor, but... They'd been
drinking that night. And the darkness...

142
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,473
I have to be in Ankara in the morning.
You know that. I told you.

143
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:06,269
I know, but everywhere looks
kind of the same to be honest.

144
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:11,310
Look, we all came out here
counting on you.

145
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:21,239
Arab, the guys got left behind.
Can't you see? Give them a shout.

146
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,438
Hey, Hayrettin!

147
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:26,191
Shape up! Move it!

148
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:32,390
Quick! Move it!

149
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:08,308
It's easy to just sit there
and talk.

150
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:10,956
Right, Arab?

151
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:12,348
What's that, boss?

152
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:15,796
I'm saying it's easy
to sit there and spout.

153
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,950
Look, did I give you any guarantees?

154
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:22,635
Did I? Am I an insurance company?

155
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:26,716
I take the suspects' statements.
The guys confess.

156
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:29,634
They say they'll show us the place.
So I say let's wrap up the case.

157
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:31,472
What else can I say?

158
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:37,833
The place has to be Girmacakil, boss.
Can't be anywhere else.

159
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:40,076
Because he's talking about
an old bridge.

160
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:44,028
Easier said than done, of course.
You attend the questioning then!

161
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:48,439
First you dump the job on me,
then you give me a hard time about it!

162
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:59,036
Give me a break, Arab! How many times
have I told you I gave up?

163
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:03,432
You're stressed out, right, boss?
Just thought you'd loosen up a bit.

164
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:16,554
Ah, hello? Hello.

165
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:21,353
It's dragging on, you know.
That's why I haven't called.

166
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:24,830
You should go to bed.
Tonight's going to be a bit..

167
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:29,958
I'm saying go to bed. Go to bed.
Sweetie, this. It won't end soon.

168
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:36,560
Where am I? On the road. In the car
with Arab Ali. We're out looking.

169
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:39,989
We're heading towards Girmacakil.

170
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:43,039
Not Diyarbakir, Girmacakil.

171
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:45,039
Hello?

172
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:49,190
How am I supposed to call?
Look, there's no signal.

173
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:53,078
Oh, that.
I was going to yesterday but..

174
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:56,677
OK, the doctor's here with me now.
I'll take care of it.

175
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:58,956
I didn't forget.

176
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:03,557
I didn't forget, dearest. Would I?
What way is that to talk?

177
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,594
OK, first thing tomorrow I'll..

178
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:10,277
OK, I'll take care of it.

179
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:13,080
I didn't forget
for goodness sake. OK.

180
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:16,313
How's the boy?
Hello?

181
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:33,752
Hey, doctor.
My boy's out of pills. I..

182
00:18:36,560 --> 00:18:39,996
I meant to stop by yesterday
for a prescription, but forgot again.

183
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:42,874
The wife keeps asking, of course.

184
00:18:43,240 --> 00:18:47,233
-Can we sort it out in the morning?
-Sure, no problem.

185
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:51,715
Thanks. Let me get the thing
or it won't be...

186
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:55,191
What's going on now?
Why's he stopped?

187
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:06,965
What's up?

188
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:11,437
I always get lost on this road.
Why don't you go first, chief?

189
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:22,591
You know none of the roads and still
you get to drive for the courthouse!

190
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:30,430
What's holding them up?

191
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:45,031
How many times is that now?
Three or four?

192
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:48,073
I've been counting, sir.
It's five including this time.

193
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:51,829
Doctor, that's prostate, right?
The prosecutor's thing?

194
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:55,631
It depends. Maybe, maybe not.

195
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:00,869
Five times and it still depends?

196
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:02,872
Well, without an examination..

197
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:07,511
I get up once a night.
Twice if I've drunk a lot of water.

198
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,672
That's normal, isn't it?

199
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:13,310
Right, once a night is fine.
Quite normal.

200
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:18,356
But after a certain age
it's worth getting checked.

201
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:24,150
You're coming in the morning, right?
I can examine you then.

202
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:26,709
No, God forbid!

203
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:29,476
-Why?
-I know how it's done.

204
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:31,199
Oh, right.

205
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,517
There's nothing wrong with me.

206
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:36,833
But check the prosecutor, I'd say.

207
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,233
He's coming.

208
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:58,631
Is it above the road or below?
Let's hear that first.

209
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:00,748
Huh?

210
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:03,198
You came this way.

211
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:06,433
-Down there..
-You're saying it's down there?

212
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:11,157
What about the tree?
Where's the round tree?

213
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:15,353
The tree there, you can see the top.
Can we look there?

214
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:16,720
-That tree down there?
-Yes.

215
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:19,752
Headlights, sergeant!
Headlights down below!

216
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:22,434
Mehmet, point the lights down below.

217
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:25,194
-Diggers, over here!
-Mr. Naci!

218
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:28,837
-Shall we bring Suspect Two this time?
-No, not necessary.

219
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:31,151
-What's your name?
-Hayrettin, chief.

220
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:32,520
-Fahrettin?
-Hayrettin, chief.

221
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:35,752
Why did you both bring shovels?
Huh? Fahrettin?

222
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:36,959
Hayrettin, chief.

223
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:39,679
I'm asking you something
and you correct me, son of a bitch.

224
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:43,515
If you can't dig up the ground here,
I'll use you as a pickaxe.

225
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:46,148
Got that, Fahrettin?

226
00:22:48,280 --> 00:22:51,477
Captain, switch to full-beam!
Is that full-beam?

227
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:54,473
-Come down a bit.
-Is that full-beam?

228
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:59,111
Switch to full-beam!
Point them at the trees!

229
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:03,191
What's going on?
Where are they?

230
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:06,716
-Down there, looking around.
-Is this the place?

231
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:09,513
No idea, doctor.

232
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:12,599
First the guy talks about fields,
now he says it's the hillside.

233
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:13,960
I don't get it.

234
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:16,833
Hey, Arab.

235
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:19,948
There's a bunch of sculptures
over there.

236
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:21,793
Sculptures?

237
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:26,470
Oh right, yes.
There's a lot around here.

238
00:24:59,520 --> 00:25:02,398
They're paying you overtime,
right, doctor?

239
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:06,437
I don't know. I expect so.

240
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:15,030
They will.

241
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:17,597
They should.

242
